. Then the charge of splaying node \ufeff\nx\nx\ufeff is at most \ufeff\n1+3(r\u2032(x)\u2212r(x))\n1+3(r\n\u2032\n(x)\u2212r(x))\ufeff .\n\n\n\n\nWe give a proof, using the auxiliary Lemma*: \n\n\n\n\nThe charge of splaying \ufeff\nx\nx\ufeff is \ufeff\n3(r\u2032(x)\u2212r(x))\n3(r\n\u2032\n(x)\u2212r(x))\ufeff .\nThe charge of rotating at \ufeff\nx\nx\ufeff is \ufeff\n1+3(r\u2032(x)\u2212r(x))\n1+3(r\n\u2032\n(x)\u2212r(x))\ufeff .", "updatedAt": 1714668288175}
